cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper presents a novel deep learning architecture for complex-valued data, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields such as machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), numerical analysis (cs.NA), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on developing a new convolution operator and fully connected layer operator for complex-valued data, which are fundamental building blocks in deep learning models for computer vision and signal processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.NA, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
